# Test Strategy Design Skill

## Purpose
Guide an AI agent through designing a comprehensive testing strategy for a codebase.

## Sections to Generate

### When to Use This Skill
Describe scenarios: setting up testing for a new project, improving test coverage, choosing test types, defining test boundaries.

### Test Pyramid
- Unit tests: fast, isolated, test single units of logic
- Integration tests: verify component interactions, database queries, API calls
- End-to-end tests: validate complete user workflows, minimal count
- Contract tests: verify API boundaries between services

### Choosing What to Test
Decision framework:
1. Business-critical paths: always test thoroughly
2. Complex logic: unit test with edge cases
3. External integrations: integration test with real/container dependencies
4. Happy paths: E2E for critical user journeys
5. Skip: trivial getters/setters, framework boilerplate, generated code

### Test Organization
- Mirror source structure in test directories
- Shared fixtures and builders
- Test helpers for common setup
- Clear naming: TestFunction_Scenario_ExpectedBehavior

### Test Quality Indicators
- Tests break when behavior changes (not when implementation changes)
- Each test verifies one behavior
- Tests are independent and can run in any order
- Fast feedback loop (unit tests < 5s, integration < 30s)

### Anti-patterns to Avoid
- Testing implementation details instead of behavior
- Mocking everything (test nothing real)
- Shared mutable state between tests
- Flaky tests from timing or external dependencies

### Verification
How to validate test strategy: coverage of critical paths, fast CI feedback, tests as documentation of behavior.
